args:
Fluffy little troublemakers are causing chaos
around town, and Sam is at the heart of it.
Turns out that when people violate a certain
taboo, it creates multiple naughty versions of
the creature. Armed with this info, the party
goes to find the original and end the havoc.
That should do it for the fiends.
By my finest servingware! The talisman\nat the entrance to the woods has been\ntorn down!
Hinomotoan sorcerers made it for\nQuinbell to keep fiends away.\nSuch a nasty prank to steal it!
No one cares about your pranks.\nWhere the heck is Sam?
Oh, look! It's Sam! ...Heeey, buddy!\nYou hungry? Want some nougat?
*chomp* *horf* *smack* *slobber*\nAw, crapola! My claws are all sticky now!
THIS is the amazing Sam you\nwouldn't shut up about?
This creature is as fluffy as Sam, but\nI'm not certain that—I say! You there!\nStop wiping your hands on that!

It is most certainly NOT—it is the talisman
used to ward off fiends! As you are clearly
the party at fault for all this ruckus,
I will thank you to hand it over this instant!
You givin' me orders, ya dumb dummy?\nKyaaa ha! Stupid! Moron! IDIOT BRIGADE!
And you! Emo kid! My morning nougat\nain't chocolate—it's nuts, ya nerd!
Maybe fire up that pea-brain of yours and\nthe answer'll come to ya. ...OR NOT!\nKyaaaaa ha ha ha! Later, suckers!
How did that thing know about\nSam's food rotation...?
Hey, Mym! Where've you been?\nYou missed a heckuva show.
I was getting ready for my festival date,\nbut there's no time for that anymore!
Imma paint this town red, baby!\nAaaaaw yeaaaaah!
Nooo! My precious tomatoes!\nStop throwing them!
First one to get their butt chomped wins\na prize! Giddyup, big boy!
Say, laaaaadies. How's it hangin'?\nWhat say you'n me go grab a nice\ncup'a tea and get to know each other?
It's that rude fuzzball from before—\nbut MORE of them!
Say, no! Knock that off right now,\nyou little monster!
Oh, you're in a world'a hurt now, boss.\nI'm gonna give you the ol' double tomato!
These creatures multiply indefinitely.\nLong ago, they led to the destruction\nof an entire kingdom.
You know what these things are, Mym?
They are called Styx. And despite how they\nmay look at the moment, they're actually\nthe young form of an elegant dragon.
Wait, so they're dragon babies?\nBut then why are they being so...rude?

By nature Styx is a well-behaved dragon—
but when people violate a particular
taboo, it makes these little devils
split off from her.
Hrm. You know what, darling?\nI don't remember that part.
That would seem to be the important\npart to remember... Okay, so anyway,\nall these Styxes split from Sam?
Sam...? Wait, do you actually know\nthe original of these little terrors?
Um...no? It's... I mean, it's just Sam,\nso it's not...you know. Stuff.
Heavens, you truly WERE raised in a barn!\nHere is the situation, my good woman...
Well, that certainly solves one question:\nSam is clearly the original.
I don't understand. Me and Sam have\nbeen living together for a few days,\nand we always got along great.

Are you trying to say the taboo was broken
by MOI? Ha! Unlike you and your slovenly
ways, I went to great pains to take the
utmost care of the beast!
That's not what I was trying to say, gosh!\nAnd do you have to be insulting about it?!

Some things that are positive to humans
are viewed as negative by dragons—and
it can take a little time for the effects of
this to make themselves known.

In any case, it's time to split up and look
for the original. I'm certain that little
critter holds the key to resolving this
entire unpleasant matter.
We don't know this town very well,\nso it'll be more efficient if we partner\nup with some of the locals.
This a good way to go, Eugene?
(The prince has that hard-to-approach\nthing going on and the dragon lady is WAY\ntoo much, so I went with the faerie.)
You're pretty different, aren't you?\nFrom when you were talking to\nthat Catherine lady, I mean.
Nuh-uh! It's just... I mean... Look,\nthat idiot brigade of a lady just\nmakes me really mad sometimes.
I dunno if it's 'cause she's the mayor's\ndaughter or what, but she's overbearing\nand haughty and out of her dang MIND!
But despite that, she's super social.\nAnd she doesn't let anything stop her\nfrom making herself heard.
Wait, do you hate her or not?
Even when he has something to say, he\nsimply sits there fidgeting and mumbling\nand being a complete craven!
THEN he has the gall to blame everyone\nelse for bad things that happen! Oh, I DO\nworry for that idiot child's future! Grrrr!
He didn't seem all that bad to me.

Well, he is, I assure you. Take you, for
example: Even though you are royalty and
of some talent, you weren't just accepted
unconditionally by your comrades, no?

Gutless Eugene does not understand that!
He won't expend the effort to get noticed
and tortures himself because of it. He's
naught but a scanty, shabby, wisp of a boy!
*I* make the effort, so why can't he?!
Have things always been bad\nbetween Eugene and Catherine?

They were pretty close as kids, but ever
since they went off to different schools, 
Eugene started to feel cut off from the
people around him.
Whereas Catherine drew everyone to her\nlike honey draws flies. And the more that\nhappened, the more the gap widened.
You humans really are a handful... Hmm?
I feel a strange sensation from\nthat restaurant over there.
Oh, what a cutie! Is this Sam?
Yes, this is most certainly the original.\nLet's tell my darling at once and—
Tsk tsk, ladies! It's rude to walk in\nand out of an establishment without\nplacing an order.
Now just take a seat right over there—\nI'll have some appetizers out to you\nlickety-split!
